%N A394361 Numbers k such that the values of d(k^2+1) set records, where d(k) is the number of divisors of k (A000005).
%C A394361 No prime factor of a(n)^2 + 1 is of the form 4*k + 3. - _David A. Corneth_, Mar 19 2026
%C A394361 a(28) <= 2280635557. - _David A. Corneth_, Mar 21 2026
%e A394361 993 is in this sequence because 993^2 + 1 = 986050 which has 48 divisors, and there is no number k between 1 and 992 where k^2 + 1 has >= 48 divisors.
%o A394361 (PARI) print1(r=1); for(n=3, 1e5, if(numdiv(n^2+1)>r, r=numdiv(n^2+1); print1(", "n)))
